{
  "texts": [
    "The modules comprising convolution layers and pooling layers are inspired by the visual cortex, with its alternation of simple and complex neurons.",
    "The convolutional layers serve as feature extractors as the neurons with their receptive fields are arranged into feature maps.",
    "The pooling layers are used to reduce the spatial resolution of these feature maps.",
    "Max pooling, as used here, preserves the maximum value within a receptive field only.",
    "The dense layers that follow interpret the features and provide the high-level reasoning, i.e., in this case the classification."
  ]
}